babysit /ˈbeɪbɪsɪt/

(babysitting,babysat,babysits) 

1. V-T/V-I If you babysit for someone or babysit their children, you look after their children while they are out. 代人临时照看 (别人的孩子); 代人临时照看小孩 

例： I promised to babysit for Mrs. Plunkett. 我答应了为普伦基特太太临时照看孩子。 

例： She had been babysitting him and his four-year-old sister. 她曾一直代为临时照看他和他4岁的妹妹。 

2. babysitter N-COUNT 临时保姆 

例： It can be difficult to find a good babysitter. 可能难以找到一个好的临时保姆。

